Large amounts of experimental and animal evidence have confirmed that iron accumulation is associated with bone loss.

 However, it is still lack of the clinical studies relating iron accumulation to bone loss, especially in the pathological conditions during our Chinese.

 In this study, the investigators aim to assess the association between the levels of serum ferritin and bone mineral density in Chinese healthy postmenopausal women.

